SUMMARY:Postgres Conference: 2026!
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Postgres\nThe one\, the only\, [Postgres Conference](h
 ttps://postgresconf.og/) returns to Silicon Valley in 2026!\n\nSince 2007\
 , Postgres Conference has been the destination for connecting with the Pos
 tgres Ecosystem in North America. Join us for a three day event which incl
 udes training\, breakout sessions and tutorials. Tracks include:\n\n* **Po
 stgres Extensions Day:** Do you develop Postgres Extensions?\nDo you want 
 to develop Postgres Extensions?\nThis day/track is for you!\n* **Dev:** Al
 l about developing with PostgreSQL. This can be about using extensions lik
 e pg_vector to increase your search performance to how to write a new data
  type.\n* **Ops:** Talks on the operational practices of Postgres and rela
 ted technologies.\n* **Essentials:** Datatypes\, How do I and data types o
 h my! If it is in the docs\, or should be an isn't... this is where you el
 aborate on all the glory that is Postgres Essentials. Do not overlook this
  track it is job security.\n* **Life and Fun:** Nothing about Postgres goe
 s here. Do you want to talk about your beehive\, backyard garden\, homeste
 ad\, solar\, latest IoT project\, mountain biking or camping? This is the 
 place.\n* **Professional Development & Wellness:** Career enhancement\, de
 aling with burnout and the false ideal of a work life balance. This is whe
 re you find peers to help with all kinds of life problems and opportunitie
 s.\n* Check out the [full program schedule](https://postgresconf.org/confe
 rences/postgresconf_2026/schedule/events)\n* [General admission](https://p
 ostgresconf.org/conferences/postgresconf_2026/tickets) registration covers
  all sessions including training\, as well as lunch buffet\, coffee\, tea\
 , and non-alcoholic beverages\n\nThank you to our growing list of sponsors
 \, including:\n\n* **Conference Sponsor:** [Amazon Web Services (AWS)](htt
 ps://aws.amazon.com/)\n* **Postgres Extensions Day Sponsor:** [Constructiv
 e](https://constructive.io/)\n* **Partner Sponsors:**\n* [Command Prompt\,
  Inc.](https://commandprompt.com/)\n* [FUJITSU](https://www.postgresql.fas
 tware.com/)\n* [NEXTGRES](http://nextgres.com/www/)\n* [pgEdge ](https://p
 gedge.com/)\n* [Quest ](https://quest.com/)\n* [Redgate ](https://www.red-
 gate.com/)\n* [VeloDB](https://www.velodb.io/)\n* [yugabyteDB](https://www
 .yugabyte.com/)\n* **Additional Sponsors:**\n* [supabase](https://supabase
 .com/)\n* [dbtune](https://www.dbtune.com/)\n* **Wellness Sponsor:** [Unli
 mited with Exceptions](https://unlimitedwithexceptions.com/)\n\n**Note:** 
 A limited number of sponsorship opportunities are still available. Downloa
 d the sponsorship prospectus and reach out via [this page](https://postgre
 sconf.org/conferences/postgresconf_2026/sponsorships).
